 :tx/rationale "Create task: RDI-6: Mode escalation signals — detect override patterns and recommend resolution mode changes. BACKGROUND: When humans or higher-authority agents override automated resolutions, the pattern indicates the current mode is inappropriate. The escalation_signal function analyzes the precedent base for a given attribute and fires when the override rate exceeds 0.3. This is the self-tuning feedback loop: resolution→Decision, override→counter-Decision, detection→escalation signal→guidance gap→mode change recommendation. APPROACH: (1) Add :resolution/override-count (Long, One) to schema. (2) Implement escalation_signal(store, attribute) -> Option<EscalationSignal>. EscalationSignal: attribute, current_mode, recommended_mode, override_count, total_count, confidence. (3) Recommendation logic: override_rate > 0.3 AND current=LWW → Lattice; override_rate > 0.5 AND current=Lattice → Deliberation; override_rate < 0.1 → downgrade to LWW. (4) Wire into methodology_gaps() as a new gap category: resolution_escalation_count. (5) Wire into braid status: show 'resolution: N attributes need mode review' when escalation signals exist. ACCEPTANCE: (A) No overrides → no signal. (B) 4/10 overrides on LWW attribute → EscalationSignal with recommended=Lattice. (C) 6/10 overrides on Lattice → recommended=Deliberation. (D) 0/10 overrides → signal to downgrade. (E) Shows in braid status. DEPENDS-ON: RDI-5. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/resolution.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/status.rs"
